Standard and Poor's Corp said it cut toCCC-plus from B-minus Lanesborough Corp's 50 mln dlrs of seniorsubordinated notes.    S and P said the downgrade reflected Lanesborough's plannedpurchase of Ampex Corp from Allied-Signal Inc &lt;ALD> for 479 mlndlrs.    "The acquisition represents a dramatic departure frommanagement's stated financial policies," S and P said. It alsosaid that Lanesborough is making a major investment in aventure with extremely high financial risk.    The company's implied senior debt rating is B. Reuter&#3;